    "client_msg_id": "0ed39d71-3233-4cca-b1e7-6dd479ad12ba",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I share so much of the sentiment expressed in the blog post.\n&gt; Why is the filesystem preserved between restarts but the contents of RAM not automatically persisted?\n\nOr.. why is persistence still a second class citizen.\n\n&gt; restore previous session\n\nI dream of working in systems with deep versioning. I.e. built on a substrate that maintains fine grained versions of the whole system so you can roll back to any point in the past.",
