    "client_msg_id": "bfee0b89-30bc-45c8-8974-9420e51dad4c",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Trouble is, you have to define your \"rollback boundary\". I guess that you'd just arbitrarily define it as \"this machine\" or \"this program or process\". But then you run into trouble when the rest of the world or surrounding processes and programs stubbornly refuse to roll back with you!\n\nBasically you'd find it hard to roll back that email you sent - retraction is hard!",
    "user": "UE6EFEPTQ",
