  {
    "client_msg_id": "001b8eec-86e4-4f2a-9657-dcc706771056",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Yes I'd expect a rollback to be like a new rollback commit to source control because reality is append only. Also we can't rollback external state. But we could still have the notion of versions very deep within our systems and that would give us a lot more power than we currently have. I mean current OSes only have the notion of current state and then we add versioning on top in various ad hoc ways via source control or package managers, file system snapshots and so on.",
    "user": "U8A5MS6R1",
